---

# 13. Coverage Exclusions

The following are excluded:

* Reserved register bits
* Undefined DMA states
* Illegal protocol sequences intentionally prevented by BFM

---

# 14. Coverage Closure Criteria

Coverage closure achieved when:

Register Coverage

```
100%
```

Register Field Coverage

```
100%
```

APB Coverage

```
>=95%
```

AXI Coverage

```
>=95%
```

Interrupt Coverage

```
100%
```

DMA State Coverage

```
100%
```

Overall Functional Coverage

```
>=95%
```

---

# 15. Coverage Review Checklist

Before signoff verify:

✓ All registers accessed

✓ All register fields exercised

✓ All APB transaction types covered

✓ All AXI transaction types covered

✓ All interrupts covered

✓ All DMA states covered

✓ All major cross coverage bins covered

✓ Coverage goals achieved

